Introduction

B.D.U is a four-member project vocal boy group. Formed through Mnet's reality survival show Build Up : Vocal Boy Group Survivor, they debuted on June 26, 2024, with the mini album "Wishpool".

The members of B.D.U are Jay Chang of ONE PACT, Bitsaeon of M.O.N.T, Seunghun of CIX, and Kim Minseo.

Their group name stands for "Boys Define Universe" and their fandom name "B.U" stands for "B.D.U with U" It means fans moving forward with the B.D.U.

The group will be active for two years and will be managed by Orca Music.
